FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - TUNISIA (09): SPREAD, SEROTYPE O, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***********************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 22 Jul 2014
Source: The Cattle Site [edited]
http://www.thecattlesite.com/news/46195/fmd-outbreaks-in-tunisian-farms-affect-cattle


The Tunisian veterinary authorities have reported 7 outbreaks of foot and mouth disease [FMD] at farms in Sfax, Jendouba, Kairouan, Mannouba and Medenine.

The World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE) received follow-up report no. 8 on Mon 21 Jul 2014. According to the report, the affected population consists of cattle and sheep. According to the report, a total of 158 cattle were found susceptible, out of which 37 cases were reported. Illegal movement of animals has been identified as the main cause of the outbreaks.

Some of the control measures applied include quarantine, movement control inside the country, vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), and disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s). None of the affected animals have received treatment.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Since the start of the event, reportedly on 25 Apr 2014, Tunisia has reported 114 outbreaks of FMD serotype O spread throughout most parts of the country. All reports submitted so far to the OIE, and an interactive map showing the reported outbreaks, are available at http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review/viewsummary?fupser=&dothis=&reportid=15183.

ProMED-mail's request for information on the efficacy of the preventive vaccine extensively used in Tunisia, as well as of the vaccine applied in response to the outbreak, is pending. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2628691,71.]
